This paper is about benchmarking HPC systems for scientific DL workloads, which involves both high performance computing (HPC) and artificial intelligence (AI) aspects. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), which focuses on designing and analyzing algorithms and systems for distributed and parallel computing. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), which are all related to AI and scientific computing.
